Package net.derquinse.common.base

Basic utility libraries and interfaces.

See:
          Description

Interface Summary
Builder<T> A class that builds objects of a certain type.
Disposable<T> Interface to provide objects that must be disposed when no longer in use.
PartialFunction<F,T> A partial function is a unary function where the domain does not include all values of the source type.
 

Class Summary
ByteString Immutable array of bytes.
ByteString.Output Builder based on an output stream.
CIString A string holder that implements equals ignoring case.
Digests Utility class for dealing with message digests.
ForwardingFunction<F,T> An abstract base class for implementing the decorator pattern for functions.
ForwardingPartialFunction<F,T> An abstract base class for implementing the decorator pattern for partial functions.
IntegerWaterMark An int value together with its hictoric maximum and minimum values.
LongWaterMark An long value together with its hictoric maximum and minimum values.
MoreFunctions Static utility methods pertaining to Function instances.
MorePredicates Static utility methods pertaining to Predicate instances.
NotInstantiable Marker class for not instantiable objects.
